snippet.textDisplay:
Your teeth not fitting together is something YOU NEED TO GET FIXED. Especially if your afraid of the dentist, your jaw closes with a whole lot of force, and if they don't fit right, that force is gonna break something in fairly short order. I'd also recommend finding a place that isn't one of those corporate chain places, which it sounds like you were at. The Doctors at those places get pressured to wring as much money out of their patients as possible, and while it's illegal for dentists to give you a procedure you truly don't need, they can and do push the limits. Though a smaller private practice will be more expensive, and much less likely to take Medicaid if you're on that.



source, am daughter of dentist, do volunteer where she works
